WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:03.670
[ALARM CLOCK BEEPING]

00:03.670 --> 00:05.172
[BEEPING STOPS]

00:05.172 --> 00:08.008
Ah. Ten more minutes. Nice.

00:08.008 --> 00:09.842
[BEEPING]

00:09.842 --> 00:10.677
[BEEPING STOPS]

00:10.677 --> 00:12.720
Ah. Ten more minutes.

00:12.720 --> 00:15.140
[IN FALSETTO]
Sweet.

00:18.601 --> 00:21.188
[ALARM CLOCK BEEPS]

00:21.979 --> 00:24.649
[BEEPING]

00:27.819 --> 00:28.528
[BEEPING]

00:28.528 --> 00:30.863
Rise and shine, lazy.
Let's go.

00:30.863 --> 00:33.741
[SEÑOR HAPPY'S "HOW MANY WAYS"
PLAYING]

00:33.741 --> 00:38.121
♪♪ How many ways
To say, "I love you?" ♪♪

00:38.538 --> 00:44.001
♪♪ How many ways
To say that I'm not scared? ♪♪

00:44.001 --> 00:46.504
♪♪ With you by my side ♪♪

00:46.504 --> 00:48.215
♪♪ There is no denyin' ♪♪

00:48.215 --> 00:52.635
♪♪ I can't wait
For me and you ♪♪

00:57.849 --> 01:01.103
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

01:01.769 --> 01:03.146
And I was only 9,

01:03.146 --> 01:06.858
but I knew it was the last time
that I would spend with her.

01:06.858 --> 01:09.111
So I held back my tears

01:09.111 --> 01:11.529
and I took her tiny paw
in my hand

01:11.529 --> 01:13.990
and I said, "Sprinkles--"

01:13.990 --> 01:15.492
[YAWNS]

01:15.492 --> 01:18.786
I said, "Sprinkles,
you are my best--"

01:18.786 --> 01:19.662
[YAWNING]

01:19.662 --> 01:20.830
Really, Audrey?

01:20.830 --> 01:22.832
Sorry.
RUSSELL: Don't apologize.

01:22.832 --> 01:25.418
You said what
we were all thinking.

01:25.418 --> 01:27.587
No, go ahead, Jen.
Finish your story.

01:27.587 --> 01:30.715
She died,
the end, whatever.

01:30.715 --> 01:32.217
No, babe,
it's not your story.

01:32.217 --> 01:33.968
I'm just--
I'm really tired,

01:33.968 --> 01:35.052
thanks to you.
RUSSELL: Yeah?

01:35.052 --> 01:38.390
The old guy managed to crank up
his rig last night?

01:38.390 --> 01:42.101
How would you like
to go meet Sprinkles?

01:42.101 --> 01:43.186
[LAUGHS]
Please continue.

01:43.186 --> 01:46.063
Jeff likes to set the alarm
way before he has to get up,

01:46.063 --> 01:47.815
and then he hits the snooze
over and over.

01:47.815 --> 01:50.902
I can never get back to sleep.
It's great when I wake up

01:50.902 --> 01:52.779
and realize I got
10 more minutes.

01:52.779 --> 01:53.780
It's not a great feeling.

01:53.780 --> 01:56.741
It happened to me three times
during her story.

01:56.741 --> 01:59.076
Smell you later, losers.

01:59.076 --> 02:02.330
When you do that,
I can't get back to sleep.

02:02.330 --> 02:05.750
Can't you set the alarm for when
you actually have to get up?

02:05.750 --> 02:08.711
I wouldn't get
the extra bonus sleep.

02:08.711 --> 02:10.838
No, you'd get
the same amount.

02:10.838 --> 02:14.301
Yes, but I wouldn't
know it.

02:14.301 --> 02:15.343
I get that.

02:15.343 --> 02:16.803
Stay out of this.

02:16.803 --> 02:18.680
But I'm supporting you.

02:18.680 --> 02:20.557
Still.

02:20.557 --> 02:21.933
Who controls your alarm?

02:21.933 --> 02:24.227
Well, it varies.
How's that?

02:24.227 --> 02:25.978
We don't have
set sides of the bed.

02:25.978 --> 02:27.605
We sort of
lie down wherever.

02:27.605 --> 02:30.567
What are you,
farm animals?

02:31.067 --> 02:32.109
God, what do you care?

02:32.109 --> 02:34.279
Couples have set sides
of the bed.

02:34.279 --> 02:35.863
Come on,
to each their own, Jeff.

02:35.863 --> 02:39.242
Absolutely not.
Please, walk me through this.

02:39.242 --> 02:43.871
You get ready for bed. You put
your sweats on, whatever...

02:43.871 --> 02:44.997
No, we sleep naked.

02:44.997 --> 02:47.459
I'm sorry, what?

02:47.459 --> 02:49.168
Totally naked.

02:49.168 --> 02:51.754
Except for a pair
of moisturizing gloves.

02:51.754 --> 02:52.755
Oh, do those work?

02:52.755 --> 02:54.966
I don't know. Ask Adam.

02:54.966 --> 02:55.883
Oh, I'm good.

02:55.883 --> 02:58.094
So there's no barrier

02:58.094 --> 02:59.637
between your business

02:59.637 --> 03:00.388
and your bed?

03:00.388 --> 03:02.849
Correct.
So your sheets become

03:02.849 --> 03:05.727
a giant pair of underpants?

03:05.727 --> 03:07.437
What do you care
what we do?

03:07.437 --> 03:08.480
Just stay out of this.

03:08.480 --> 03:10.732
But this is my thing.
JEFF: Whatever.

03:10.732 --> 03:13.109
No sides, no clothes,
no rules.

03:13.109 --> 03:15.695
Basically your bedroom
is Thunderdome.

03:15.695 --> 03:18.114
Thunderdome,
like that movie?

03:18.114 --> 03:19.657
Like, 100 years ago?

03:19.657 --> 03:20.617
Whatever.

03:20.617 --> 03:22.910
Filthy, naked hippies.

03:22.910 --> 03:25.079
Would you leave them alone?

03:25.079 --> 03:28.082
Fine, but you know what?
This isn't over.

03:28.082 --> 03:30.209
How is it not over?

03:30.877 --> 03:33.170
Your burger
is really undercooked.

03:33.170 --> 03:34.046
No, it's fine.

03:34.046 --> 03:36.132
No, babe, it's raw.
Just send it back.

03:36.132 --> 03:39.261
Risk upsetting the waitress?
Adam would never do anything

03:39.261 --> 03:41.388
that would make someone
not like him.

03:41.388 --> 03:43.223
It still happens, though.

03:43.223 --> 03:45.767
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

03:47.852 --> 03:50.438
Timmy, get in here.

03:53.024 --> 03:53.733
Yes, sir?

03:53.733 --> 03:56.110
What are all these people
lining up for?

03:56.110 --> 03:58.321
Ooh, is there a concert?
I wanna see it.

03:58.321 --> 04:00.114
Is it food?
I wanna eat it.

04:00.114 --> 04:02.534
Is it an author I don't know
signing some book

04:02.534 --> 04:05.370
I've never heard of?
I gotta get a copy.

04:05.370 --> 04:07.830
Sir, calm down.

04:07.830 --> 04:09.291
Why, are they calming down?

04:09.291 --> 04:11.668
They're waiting to purchase
the latest version

04:11.668 --> 04:15.004
of the newest must-have phone.
Ooh, I must have it.

04:15.004 --> 04:17.131
Very well, I'll put it
on my to-do list.

04:17.131 --> 04:19.967
No, no, no. Go get in line
right now. I want it now.

04:19.967 --> 04:22.554
The phone doesn't go
on sale until tomorrow morning.

04:22.554 --> 04:25.890
While you were mouthing off, two
more people just got in line.

04:25.890 --> 04:28.310
You actually want me to stand
out there overnight?

04:28.310 --> 04:31.479
Well, I'm afraid I can't.
My uncle is in town--

04:31.479 --> 04:32.480
Oh, okay, oh.

04:32.480 --> 04:34.607
No, let me just call Galileo,

04:34.607 --> 04:35.358
tell him he was wrong.

04:35.358 --> 04:39.487
Apparently all the planets
revolve around Timmy.

04:39.487 --> 04:42.824
You should actually be calling
Copernicus, sir,

04:42.824 --> 04:45.327
because it was he
who first postulated--

04:45.327 --> 04:48.955
Stop raping my ears
with your words.

04:48.955 --> 04:51.958
Now let's go get me
that phone.

04:51.958 --> 04:53.501
But-- But--
But, but.

04:53.501 --> 04:55.670
What are butts for?

04:57.755 --> 04:59.382
Butts are for pooping.

04:59.382 --> 05:01.593
That's right.

05:01.593 --> 05:04.053
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

05:04.471 --> 05:08.933
I'm just saying, enough with
all these sexy vampire shows.

05:08.933 --> 05:12.186
Am I right,
or am I right?

05:12.186 --> 05:13.938
What are you doing?

05:13.938 --> 05:16.566
I just felt like sleeping
on this side tonight.

05:16.566 --> 05:18.568
You can't. That's my side.
[LAUGHS]

05:18.568 --> 05:21.988
Look, I was thinking,
Adam and Jen are right.

05:21.988 --> 05:23.531
Why do we have
to have sides?

05:23.531 --> 05:26.326
Plus, I get to control
the alarm clock for a change.

05:26.326 --> 05:28.411
You want to be more
like Adam and Jen.

05:28.411 --> 05:29.537
Well, let's sleep naked too.

05:29.537 --> 05:32.123
Let our loose parts
flop all over the place.

05:32.123 --> 05:36.210
I just want to get
a full night's sleep for once.

05:36.210 --> 05:38.254
Our sides of the bed
are locked in.

05:38.254 --> 05:40.840
You throw out the rules,
next thing you know,

05:40.840 --> 05:43.009
it'sThunderdome.

05:43.009 --> 05:46.095
You really need to stop
watching that DVD.

05:46.095 --> 05:47.847
Look, I'm just saying

05:47.847 --> 05:51.434
we don't need
another hero.

05:51.434 --> 05:51.934
[LAUGHS]

05:51.934 --> 05:54.521
Come on. You're the one
who's always saying

05:54.521 --> 05:56.731
you wanna shake things up
in the bedroom.

05:56.731 --> 05:58.608
Yeah, like,
maybe watch some porn

05:58.608 --> 06:01.611
or invite your friend
Sheila over.

06:01.611 --> 06:04.531
Oh, just get in bed.

06:05.573 --> 06:08.284
FYI, Sheila just got engaged.

06:08.284 --> 06:09.326
Oh! Really?

06:09.326 --> 06:11.370
Oh, yeah,
because before that,

06:11.370 --> 06:14.499
it was a possibility.

06:14.499 --> 06:16.543
I know that
you're being sarcastic,

06:16.543 --> 06:19.921
but later, when I relive
that conversation,

06:19.921 --> 06:22.298
you won't be.

06:22.298 --> 06:24.216
There's not even
an indentation here.

06:24.216 --> 06:28.387
Well, there is over here
in Body Hair Canyon.

06:28.387 --> 06:30.181
What, are you molting?

06:30.181 --> 06:33.059
All you got over here
is "Sudok-oh."

06:33.059 --> 06:35.019
You know how I feel
about "Sudok-oh."

06:35.019 --> 06:38.022
Yes, you feel like an idiot
because you don't know

06:38.022 --> 06:40.525
how to pronounce it.
Here.

06:40.525 --> 06:44.278
Skim this fitness
and retain nothing.

06:48.199 --> 06:51.619
The light's hitting it
all funny.

06:51.619 --> 06:54.246
There's a draft over here.

06:54.246 --> 06:56.082
I am much further
from the bathroom.

06:56.082 --> 06:58.375
That's gonna throw off
my timing.

06:58.375 --> 06:59.586
Oh, God.

06:59.586 --> 07:03.548
[LAUGHING]
You are such a baby.

07:03.548 --> 07:04.466
Just go to sleep.

07:04.466 --> 07:09.846
I am looking forward to waking
up rested and refreshed.

07:13.349 --> 07:15.142
[CLATTERING]
AUDREY: What was that?

07:15.142 --> 07:20.231
JEFF:
I just groped the phone
instead of your boob.

07:21.941 --> 07:24.861
AUDREY:
Oh, goody, you found it.

07:24.861 --> 07:26.821
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

07:28.531 --> 07:30.700
I love these sexy
vampire shows.

07:30.700 --> 07:33.745
But don't tell Jeff,
because he doesn't like them.

07:33.745 --> 07:35.997
[ELECTRIC GUITAR BLARING
UPSTAIRS]

07:35.997 --> 07:38.332
Oh, my God,
the guy upstairs.

07:38.332 --> 07:40.627
It's, like, the third night
in a row.

07:40.627 --> 07:42.419
I know.
What a bummer, huh?

07:42.419 --> 07:45.965
Gee, I wonder which one of us
is gonna go up to talk to him.

07:45.965 --> 07:48.300
What's that supposed to mean?
Oh, come on,

07:48.300 --> 07:49.469
you're not
gonna confront him.

07:49.469 --> 07:53.264
He's just another uncooked
burger you're willing to eat.

07:53.264 --> 07:54.265
You are wrong. I got this.

07:54.265 --> 07:56.058
I don't care
what he thinks.

07:56.058 --> 07:58.978
The gloves are coming off.

08:04.526 --> 08:06.694
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

08:06.694 --> 08:07.654
You think that's bad?

08:07.654 --> 08:10.490
Last weekend,
my boss' kid had a bar mitzvah.

08:10.490 --> 08:13.493
My boss made me write
all the thank-you notes.

08:13.493 --> 08:16.203
My boss doesn't even
know my name.

08:16.203 --> 08:18.372
He just calls me
"Skidmark."

08:18.372 --> 08:19.624
Pfft. Big deal.

08:19.624 --> 08:22.752
My boss walks behind me
and smells my hair.

08:22.752 --> 08:26.213
Then he locks himself
in his office for 20 minutes.

08:26.213 --> 08:28.800
Yeah? Here's a list of things
my boss threw at me

08:28.800 --> 08:31.553
just last week:
his stapler, his sandwich,

08:31.553 --> 08:35.598
my sandwich, and a rock
from his Zen garden.

08:35.598 --> 08:39.018
Oh, and he smells my hair too.

08:39.018 --> 08:39.811
You win.

08:39.811 --> 08:43.064
You have the most awful boss
in New York City.

08:47.193 --> 08:48.903
Excuse me.

08:48.903 --> 08:50.029
If I may.

08:50.029 --> 08:52.824
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

08:53.991 --> 08:57.161
[ELECTRIC GUITAR BLARING]

08:59.539 --> 09:01.874
[MUSIC STOPS]

09:03.209 --> 09:05.252
Hey, uh, I'm Adam.
I live downstairs.

09:05.252 --> 09:07.880
I'm Frank.
Yeah, the thing is,

09:07.880 --> 09:09.340
your guitar.

09:09.340 --> 09:09.966
What about it?

09:09.966 --> 09:13.219
I mean,
I think you're good.

09:13.928 --> 09:14.929
Dude, you shred.

09:14.929 --> 09:16.931
Thanks. Come on in.

09:16.931 --> 09:19.475
[STRUMMING]
But the thing is,

09:19.475 --> 09:21.268
it might be a little loud.

09:21.268 --> 09:21.769
Oh, man, really?

09:21.769 --> 09:23.938
You're not gonna be one
of those guys?

09:23.938 --> 09:26.315
Okay, here's the deal.

09:26.315 --> 09:27.399
Yeah?

09:27.399 --> 09:29.235
It's not me.

09:29.235 --> 09:31.070
It's my fiancée, you know.

09:31.070 --> 09:35.282
She's trying to watch one of
those romantic vampire shows.

09:35.282 --> 09:36.576
Oh, I hate those.

09:36.576 --> 09:38.703
Yeah, me too.

09:38.703 --> 09:39.912
Doing this for your lady, huh?

09:39.912 --> 09:42.456
Yeah, you get that, right?
Totally.

09:42.456 --> 09:43.082
Women, huh?

09:43.082 --> 09:46.127
Yeah, I feel you, bro.
I'll unplug.

09:46.127 --> 09:47.795
Hey, thanks a lot, man.

09:47.795 --> 09:48.921
No worries, man, I get it.

09:48.921 --> 09:51.674
I've had my share
of psycho girlfriends.

09:51.674 --> 09:55.344
Well, I mean, I really
wouldn't call mine psycho.

09:55.928 --> 09:57.554
At least not to her face.

09:57.554 --> 09:58.890
[BOTH LAUGH]

09:58.890 --> 10:00.850
[SNIFFS]

10:00.850 --> 10:03.560
I smell...lavender?

10:03.560 --> 10:05.479
Oh, yeah, no, I was just...

10:05.479 --> 10:08.482
You know,
punching some candles.

10:10.442 --> 10:13.738
And because Mr. Dunbar's arms
are so short,

10:13.738 --> 10:18.618
guess who had to apply
the ointment for him?

10:18.618 --> 10:20.953
Directly on his--?

10:20.953 --> 10:24.581
Every four hours.

10:24.581 --> 10:28.085
That is absolutely
horrifying.

10:28.085 --> 10:32.006
Now, let me tell you
what my second day was like.

10:32.006 --> 10:33.966
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

10:35.176 --> 10:35.843
Huh?

10:35.843 --> 10:37.929
Anyone else's business

10:37.929 --> 10:39.889
you want me all up in?

10:39.889 --> 10:41.766
What did you say to him?

10:41.766 --> 10:45.144
I just got in his face,
laid down the law.

10:45.144 --> 10:46.312
I'm impressed.

10:46.312 --> 10:47.939
You stood up for your lady.

10:47.939 --> 10:48.773
Hell, yeah, I did.

10:48.773 --> 10:53.027
Hm, so do you want
to finish watching

10:53.027 --> 10:55.237
your vampire show,

10:55.237 --> 10:57.990
or maybe...?

10:57.990 --> 11:01.285
Definitely "or maybe."

11:02.829 --> 11:04.789
But my--
My vampire show still--

11:04.789 --> 11:06.833
It's recording, right?

11:06.833 --> 11:09.335
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

11:11.963 --> 11:13.715
[ALARM CLOCK BEEPING]

11:13.715 --> 11:17.802
Oh! My God, my eye!

11:19.762 --> 11:25.351
Again, I am really,
really sorry.

11:25.351 --> 11:26.477
Okay, Jeff.

11:26.477 --> 11:29.355
How long do I have to keep
this thing on, doctor?

11:29.355 --> 11:30.439
Just one or two days.

11:30.439 --> 11:32.817
Long enough
for the cornea to heal.

11:32.817 --> 11:37.154
[IN IRISH ACCENT]
And will she still be able
to plunder doubloons?

11:37.154 --> 11:40.157
That's the follow-up
to your big apology?

11:40.157 --> 11:44.203
[NORMAL VOICE]
Take it easy,
Tom Cruise in Valkyrie.

11:47.623 --> 11:48.791
Enough, all right?

11:48.791 --> 11:51.085
My eye hurts
when I roll it.

11:51.085 --> 11:52.378
Oh, take these.

11:52.378 --> 11:54.130
Uh, they're pretty
powerful.

11:54.130 --> 11:55.256
They might
put you to sleep.

11:55.256 --> 11:59.802
Hm. Or Jen can trot out
that dead-cat story again.

11:59.802 --> 12:00.302
Thank you.

12:00.302 --> 12:02.429
JEFF:
You know,
it doesn't look so bad.

12:02.429 --> 12:05.767
Nobody'll notice if you
let me draw an eyeball on it.

12:05.767 --> 12:08.310
Jeff, you're not drawing
an eyeball on it.

12:08.310 --> 12:12.023
You're right. It would probably
scare the parrot.

12:12.606 --> 12:14.483
I'm sorry. I feel bad.

12:14.483 --> 12:17.904
And it's not even my fault.

12:18.695 --> 12:19.571
Wha--?

12:19.571 --> 12:22.741
In what way is your giant,
meaty paw

12:22.741 --> 12:24.827
smacking me in the face
not your fault?

12:24.827 --> 12:27.538
JEFF:
You're the one who wanted
to switch sides.

12:27.538 --> 12:29.623
I didn't wanna hit you
in the face.

12:29.623 --> 12:31.708
It was just force of habit.

12:34.045 --> 12:37.214
All I wanted
was one little thing.

12:37.214 --> 12:39.091
But lookit, I told you it was
a bad idea.

12:39.091 --> 12:42.261
I warned you,
but you just wouldn't listen.

12:42.261 --> 12:44.138
AUDREY:
I know.

12:44.138 --> 12:47.683
I know, I know, I know.

12:47.683 --> 12:49.601
I just should have
known better.

12:49.601 --> 12:51.187
Well, don't beat yourself up.

12:51.187 --> 12:53.355
No, I'll leave that to you.

12:54.899 --> 12:57.693
Boy, those meds
are making you mouthy.

12:57.693 --> 13:00.612
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

13:03.115 --> 13:05.034
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

13:12.333 --> 13:15.502
Check it out.
I just swiped some Jell-O.

13:20.925 --> 13:23.177
I'm not hungry.

13:23.177 --> 13:26.638
I was hoping you'd say that.

13:27.764 --> 13:29.266
Those painkillers
kick in yet?

13:29.266 --> 13:32.228
How you feeling?
Mm, I feel good.

13:32.228 --> 13:33.645
[CHUCKLES]

13:33.645 --> 13:34.563
Very, very good.

13:34.563 --> 13:37.984
Well, then this is probably
the best time to tell you

13:37.984 --> 13:39.318
that when you went to Cancún,

13:39.318 --> 13:41.612
I reported
your credit card stolen.

13:41.612 --> 13:44.323
That's why
it wouldn't work.

13:47.618 --> 13:51.122
I love pushing it
through my teeth. Watch.

13:52.414 --> 13:54.000
[KNOCKS]

13:55.584 --> 13:58.295
Hi. I'm sorry this is taking
so long, but, Mr. Bingham,

13:58.295 --> 14:03.009
I'm gonna have to come with me
to fill out some paperwork.

14:06.971 --> 14:10.349
What, is this about
the Jell-O?

14:10.641 --> 14:12.143
Hi, Mrs. Bingham,
I'm Wendy.

14:12.143 --> 14:14.937
I'm a social worker.
I wanted to check on you.

14:14.937 --> 14:16.898
[LAUGHS]
Hi, Wendy.

14:16.898 --> 14:17.481
Hi.

14:17.481 --> 14:21.027
Listen, I want you to know
that you are in a safe place.

14:21.027 --> 14:22.486
So if you're comfortable...

14:22.486 --> 14:24.071
Oh, yeah, I'm comfortable.

14:24.071 --> 14:26.282
I'm super comfy.

14:26.282 --> 14:27.658
[LAUGHS]Good.

14:27.658 --> 14:29.869
And now I wanted to ask
about your injury.

14:29.869 --> 14:32.621
Your husband did this to you,
didn't he?

14:32.621 --> 14:34.040
Oh, yeah.

14:34.040 --> 14:35.624
[LAUGHS]

14:37.126 --> 14:39.420
Big surprise.

14:39.420 --> 14:40.629
Tell me what happened.

14:40.629 --> 14:42.839
Oh, it was my fault.

14:42.839 --> 14:45.467
It is never your fault.

14:45.467 --> 14:49.388
You know, I should've kept
my mouth shut

14:49.388 --> 14:52.766
and stayed on my side
of the bed.

14:54.226 --> 14:55.852
Is that what he told you?

14:55.852 --> 14:57.521
Oh, it doesn't matter.

14:57.521 --> 15:00.274
He's really,
really sorry.

15:00.274 --> 15:03.485
And then he ate my Jell-O.

15:03.485 --> 15:07.281
Well, everything's
going to be okay now.

15:07.281 --> 15:09.491
Ah. How long is Jeff
gonna be gone?

15:09.491 --> 15:13.245
Oh, you don't have to worry
about him anymore.

15:16.582 --> 15:17.917
Mr. Bingham.

15:17.917 --> 15:19.335
Hey, what's up?

15:19.335 --> 15:21.921
You son of a bitch.

15:22.046 --> 15:24.048
You're going to have
to come with us.

15:24.048 --> 15:26.675
Oh, look, I'll pay
for the Jell-O.

15:26.675 --> 15:28.635
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

15:28.635 --> 15:30.679
So instead of attending
my own birthday party,

15:30.679 --> 15:33.682
I spent the night explaining
to three adult-film actresses

15:33.682 --> 15:37.228
that none of them got the part
because there really was,

15:37.228 --> 15:39.771
in fact, no movie.

15:39.771 --> 15:43.359
And that sums up
the last six months.

15:43.359 --> 15:45.611
All of that
in six months?

15:45.611 --> 15:46.403
TIMMY:
Yes, Veronica.

15:46.403 --> 15:49.823
Oh, and Secretary's Day?
Not even a card.

15:49.823 --> 15:50.741
Even I got a card.

15:50.741 --> 15:56.122
It said, "Take this
out of petty cash, Skidmark."

15:56.122 --> 15:56.830
Oh, come on.

15:56.830 --> 15:57.957
Are you guys
really buying this?

15:57.957 --> 16:01.168
I'm sorry? You think I've been
making these up all night?

16:01.168 --> 16:03.795
What on Earth would I stand
to gain from doing that?

16:03.795 --> 16:06.590
I don't know. Maybe you just
like the attention.

16:06.590 --> 16:09.176
Yes, that's what I crave:
attention from the gang

16:09.176 --> 16:11.303
in the "who's the biggest
loser?" contest.

16:11.303 --> 16:14.431
Sorry, Veronica, I know you've
got some irons in the fire.

16:14.431 --> 16:17.643
Whatever, dude. No boss could
ever be that bad.

16:17.643 --> 16:20.896
Well, it looks as though
you'll have a chance

16:20.896 --> 16:22.231
to judge for yourself.

16:22.231 --> 16:23.899
Here he comes now.

16:23.899 --> 16:26.943
MAN:
Where, behind that little
blond girl?

16:26.943 --> 16:29.530
No, he is
the little blond girl.

16:29.530 --> 16:30.781
Timmy.

16:30.781 --> 16:31.532
Mr. Dunbar, good day.

16:31.532 --> 16:35.995
How you doing? You okay?
I was worried about you. Here.

16:35.995 --> 16:37.454
Come on,
he brought you coffee.

16:37.454 --> 16:40.124
Give it a minute.
Yeah, this isn't coffee.

16:40.124 --> 16:41.042
This is an empty cup.

16:41.042 --> 16:42.834
I don't want to lose
my place in line

16:42.834 --> 16:46.630
if babu here decides
he needs to take a whiz.

16:46.630 --> 16:47.756
And we're off.

16:47.756 --> 16:49.591
Here's today's to-do list.

16:49.591 --> 16:52.719
Yikes, a little sticky.
Don't ask.

16:52.719 --> 16:54.471
I never do, sir.

16:54.471 --> 16:56.057
And off to the office.

16:56.057 --> 16:57.099
Oh...

16:57.099 --> 17:01.020
You seem a little
emotionally shaken.

17:01.020 --> 17:03.564
[WHISPERING]
Get her number.

17:03.564 --> 17:06.900
I am so sorry
I ever doubted you.

17:06.900 --> 17:09.111
Not at all.

17:11.113 --> 17:11.947
[SNIFFLES]

17:11.947 --> 17:13.782
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

17:13.782 --> 17:16.327
[ELECTRIC GUITAR BLARING]

17:20.247 --> 17:23.375
Look, my fiancé read you
the riot act yesterday,

17:23.375 --> 17:26.628
and I know he's not gonna be
happy when he finds out

17:26.628 --> 17:28.255
you're still--

17:28.255 --> 17:30.049
[PLAYING]

17:34.345 --> 17:36.972
And that is an example
of the kind of noise

17:36.972 --> 17:38.640
we don't wanna hear
anymore.

17:38.640 --> 17:40.059
I hope you got that straight,

17:40.059 --> 17:42.644
because I don't wanna
have to come up here--

17:42.644 --> 17:44.521
Dude, she's gone.
Oh, no!

17:44.521 --> 17:45.314
I am so screwed right now.

17:45.314 --> 17:48.400
When she gets angry, I mean,
she's like a raving--

17:48.400 --> 17:50.236
Dude, she's back.

17:50.236 --> 17:51.528
--angel.

17:51.528 --> 17:54.531
She's like
a raving angel.

17:54.531 --> 17:56.783
Hey, baby, let's go.

17:58.952 --> 18:00.996
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

18:02.623 --> 18:04.500
[SIGHS]

18:04.666 --> 18:07.128
I know wives everywhere
are sick of hearing this

18:07.128 --> 18:10.005
from their husbands,
and it may sound trite,

18:10.005 --> 18:13.509
but thanks for not
pressing charges.

18:13.509 --> 18:14.718
No problem.

18:14.718 --> 18:17.763
I didn't think it was gonna take
you so long to clear it up,

18:17.763 --> 18:23.269
but I guess you were coming down
from those painkillers, so...

18:23.269 --> 18:23.977
Sure.

18:23.977 --> 18:27.481
[LAUGHS]
That's what it was.

18:27.481 --> 18:30.234
Well, anyway.

18:30.234 --> 18:31.485
Listen, I had a--

18:31.485 --> 18:36.365
I had a lot of time to think
while I was in lockup.

18:37.408 --> 18:39.701
You were in the nurses'
break room.

18:39.701 --> 18:42.413
With a vending machine
that only took exact change,

18:42.413 --> 18:45.916
so it might as well
have been prison.

18:45.916 --> 18:48.043
Look, they fingerprinted me.

18:48.043 --> 18:50.712
Wash that off, please.
I don't wanna wake up

18:50.712 --> 18:52.214
with ink all over my boobs.

18:52.214 --> 18:54.007
Aye, aye, matey.

18:54.007 --> 18:56.677
Anyway, listen, I was thinking
that at the very least

18:56.677 --> 19:00.681
I should, uh, let you choose
which side of the bed you want.

19:00.681 --> 19:02.516
Oh, well,
I'll take my old side.

19:02.516 --> 19:06.353
Better to lose a little sleep
than the other eye.

19:06.353 --> 19:09.105
Hey, I'll tell you what.

19:09.856 --> 19:11.192
I will set the, uh, clock

19:11.192 --> 19:13.819
for the real time
that I have to get up.

19:13.819 --> 19:15.821
Thank you.

19:16.197 --> 19:19.032
So I guess no more acting
like Jen and Adam, huh?

19:19.032 --> 19:21.577
Well, there is one more thing
of theirs

19:21.577 --> 19:24.455
that I would like to try.

19:26.373 --> 19:27.791
Huh?

19:28.875 --> 19:32.171
Welcome toThunderdome.

19:33.630 --> 19:35.549
On second thought,

19:35.549 --> 19:37.384
take out the other eye.

19:37.384 --> 19:39.261
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

19:42.431 --> 19:48.270
So I guess the silver lining is,
uh, free Jell-O.

19:49.480 --> 19:50.522
Nice.

19:50.522 --> 19:53.609
Here's your phone, sir.

19:53.609 --> 19:55.652
Ah.

19:55.652 --> 19:57.988
Oh.

19:58.239 --> 20:00.532
They didn't have it
in red?

20:03.494 --> 20:05.412
[SIGHS]

20:06.580 --> 20:08.707
Timmy, come here.

20:09.875 --> 20:11.377
Yes, sir?

20:11.377 --> 20:13.379
Don't forget your bathroom.

20:13.379 --> 20:16.298
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

20:19.843 --> 20:22.388
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]
